  "title": "A COVID-19 survivors and close contacts EEG dataset",
  "description": "This dataset comprises 173 resting-state electroencephalography (EEG) recordings from COVID-19 survivors (n=87) and close contacts/healthy controls (n=86), acquired using standard 10-20 electrode montage. The study investigates EEG signatures associated with COVID-19 infection and recovery, contributing to understanding of neurophysiological alterations in post-COVID conditions. Recordings include 8 minutes of eyes-closed resting state followed by alternating eye-open/closed conditions, providing comprehensive baseline neurophysiological characterization.",
  "methods_description": "EEG was acquired using a 10-20 standard montage. Resting EEG was recorded for 8 minutes with eyes closed in all participants. Additional recordings included 2 minutes of alternating closed and open eyes, followed by 2 minutes of recovery.",
